title: Prologis Earnings beat, Revenue misses In Q3
text:
© Reuters. Prologis Earnings beat, Revenue misses In Q3

Investing.com - Prologis reported third quarter that beat analysts' expectations on Tuesday and revenue that fell short of forecasts.

The firm reported earnings per share of $0.97 on revenue of $711.7M. Analysts polled by Investing.com anticipated EPS of $0.53 on revenue of $715.88M. That compared to EPS of $0.62 on revenue of $608.97M in the same period a year earlier. The company had reported EPS of $0.62 on revenue of $700.69M in the previous quarter.

For the year, Prologis shares are up 46.9%, outperforming the which is up 19.75% year to date.

Prologis follows other major Services sector earnings this month

On Thursday, October 3, 2019, Costco reported fourth quarter EPS of $2.69 on revenue of $47.5B, compared to forecasts of EPS of $2.54 on revenue of $47.44B.

Paychex earnings beat analyst's expectations on Wednesday, October 2, 2019, with first quarter EPS of $0.71 on revenue of $992M. Investing.com analysts expected EPS of $0.69 on revenue of $991.18M
